cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.DS 

This paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques to remove clouds and recover ground observations in satellite image sequences. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel objective function for matrix completion, which involves balancing temporal smoothness with a low rank solution, indicating that it could be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with remote sensing, which could fall under the sub-category of graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper provides efficient optimization algorithms, which could be relevant to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
